caption: Longtime local family owned Chinese restaurant with a gourmet twist. The interior is crisp, clean and elegant with shiney metal chopsticks on cloth napkins. The service is professional; best of all the food is delicious and adventurous. Carry out and delivery is nicely packaged if you'd prefer to enjoy the culinary experience at home.
My absolute favorite restaurant
Very slow service, bad communication and impolite staff . Overall a very unpleasant experience. Will not come back.

Portions were lacking. Flavor was good though. The noodles for my Peking duck dish were all messed up. Some crispy, some soggy. Some really thick and some paper thin. And why was there a pound of whole green onions? I know it says green onions on the menu, and I love them, but dice them up a bit. I wish I would have taken a picture. The broth for the wonton soup was good. Probably will never order here again though. $60 for three dishes? Meh.
wow the food is spectacular without.  words I recommend you go this restaurant worth going .. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

The quality and service at this restaurant have really gone down hill over the last 6 months. I have been eating here for 6 years and have always been happy up until recently. The last few times I have ordered take out I have arrived when I was told the food would be ready only to wait another 20 minutes. Tonight I ordered my go to dish there and it just wasn't the same. Lower quality, less food, same price.  Not sure if I'll eat there again. At least not for a while.  Update: I recently ordered delivery from Friendship Chinese based on a recommendation from a friend. I told them about what I had experienced and they ensured me that things had improved.  He was right.  We ordered a shrimp noodle dish that was delicious. It was delivered quickly and all of the food was very good. I will be adding this place back into our rotation.

My family has been raving about this place for so long so I decided to try it for the first time today. We ordered take out and I knew I was in for a great experience as everything was packaged perfectly. I am not exaggerating when I say that when I had my first bite I felt like I was transported to another dimension. Their sesame chicken and spicy garlic shrimp fried rice is out of this world. I never want to eat from any other Chinese restaurant after trying this. Thanks for a great experience!
Nice...
Food must be awesome the wait time is horrendous.
Terrible service. I ordered $100+ food and they can’t find my order WITH a confirmation number. I call and get the run-around. They refuse to give me any info about my order and just hang up
"This place used to be moderately priced, small portions and pretty good food."

Ordered delivery from here for the first time. It is the best Chinese I have tried in the area.  The vegetables were super fresh and high and the meat was high quality and cooked perfectly; tender beef, all white meat chicken. The pineapple fried rice needed a little more time in the pan to get more flavor (I would still order it again) but the potstickers and Gai Lan were delicious.  The food was packaged better than any take out I have ever ordered.  Every item was in a leak proof container and then delivered in a cake box.  Love the chocolate fortune cookies!
Food is excellent her and very friendly service. I especially liked the orange chicken and mongolian beef. My new favorite Chinese restaurant!
They do not attend there patients and closed the doors at 4:45pm when it suppose to be 5pm my mother is diabetic and has heart problems and they never help her bad ppl
Good food

Wow i love waiting 3 hours for an order never to be delivered. You think they would have the courtesy to call and say we cannot deliver your food because we have no driver. Nope they took the 68 dollars thou. And now i must wait and call and be on hold with grub hub for a refund which will be processed in 3 to 5 business days. Thanks so much friendship chinese.
The WORST Orange chicken we have ever had but did  not complain to them bc times are hard for restaurants.
great service. thank you

The food was really good the duck egg rolls and the black rice and sausage was good and unique.The beef with broccoli was very good as well it's my first time ordering and it wont be my last. The best in this kneck of the woods you would have to go to china town to maybe get something as good or the same..
Everything is delicious from this place. Placed an order through Grubhub arrived fast, very neatly packaged with lots of variety of sauces. Very authentic food.

We ordered delivery directly from their website - it came pretty fast (30 min or less) and was DELICIOUS. The food had a really great depth of flavor. 2 entrees and one appetizer for 2 people ended up being 2-3 meals for us. Very happy; we'll definitely be ordering from here again!!!

We ordered for pick up last night. They were out of the pork shu mei  (understandable given todays state of affairs) but they called ahead an made a great recommendation! The food was delicious and it was good break from cooking and clean up :)

Tonight's dinner from FC was just absolutely fantastic. The food was delivered in 20 minutes- it was piping hot and so fresh. I truly believe this is one of the best Chinese restaurants in Chicago and to be close enough to get impeccable dining delivered on those snowy or exhausting days is such a treat. We got the Crab Ragoon and Egg Rolls for our starters. Having actual crab in a crab ragoon is nearly unheard of, and it's done in a way that the little purses are delicately done. The Egg Roll, light and crispy, chicken rather than the traditional deep friend pork. I choose Eggplant for my entree, the sauce was a subtle addition to this veg filled and friendly dish. My husband enjoyed his Sesame Chicken dish, all white meat, freshly prepared with great flavor. We missed dining-in but with the amount of time we spent with the gen pop with this pandemic going on, it was really nice to  be able to experience this meal at home and we only lost out on ambience, not quality.
Amazing Chinese food in Avondale

I dine in this lovely spot quite a bit! This is my favorite restaurant to grab a bite.  I visit this place many times. The food is just great, the workers are courteous and the price is reasonable. I enjoy being in this place to have a tasty meal.
Don’t eat at places that sell shark fin soup
The restaurant is superb and broad, the meals was delicious and the rates were very economical. rapidly, productive service and very welcoming staff members. I recommend this place.
They serve large portions and for affordable prices. friendly staff members. Highly recommended.
The food here is better than any place in Chinatown by a mile.
This place is worth giving a shot. They have big portions for fair rates. Regularly neat and with great atmosphere. I highly recommend this place.
Fresh food and very tasty. The book Choy and Chinese broccoli dishes really are fantastic
Best Chinese I've had in a while outside of NYC and Chinatown here.
Wonderful ambiance,  great service and the food and drink selections are terrific. Especially  the Tuesday night special all entrees $11.95.
Awesome and tasty food, I like the character the place has, and the employees were welcoming. Will surely eat here again.

This is certainly one of the coolest restaurants in the neighborhood. Always when I go there I am incredibly satisfied. They hold their high  level service and the topmost level of cooking  they offer. You surely will enjoy this this place. Warmly  recommended.
Mai Tai is good. Their lunch box is only $12, good, and plentiful.

This restaurant is VERY misleading and we will not be going back. Some of our dishes were tasty but we have quite a number of complaints. 1. Although we were told that the spring rolls are made with rice paper they felt and tasted like it was wonton wrapper (I'm really hoping they were right). 2. We were told that the mushrooms in the mushrooms tofu soup would be the same as in the Wild mushroom entree but there were only wedges of button mushrooms! They are not wild mushrooms. The waitress checked with the chef who said that they are wild but I don't know if any wild mushrooms resemble button mushrooms. 3. The soup also tasted like a simple Lipton broth with tofu and button mushrooms yet it was $7.95! Even the waitress said that the owner changed the menu not for the better and didn't update the website so entree items are prices are not the same as listed online.
Food and ambiance is amazing

Friendship has been one of my favorite Chinese restaurants for the past 7 years. Their food is deliciously satisfying and well put together. The only thing that the Christmas music for this type of restaurants setting didn't fit this atmosphere. Ummmmmm
Food is delicious but instead of fried rice they brought me white rice you Gotta make sure they bring the right stuff before you sign the receipt I didn’t even look at it in my mistake
I am just going to say if you like beef tenderloin then this can most likely be one of your top choices for a steak dinner place.
Food was pretty good but way over priced
Great food, excellent service & reasonably priced. What more could you ask for?

Simple put, my favorite Chinese restaurant in the city. The XO Beef Chow Fun is a must, noodles are crispy but not greasy, beef flavorful and tender, and sauce wonderful! Definitely pair it with the Peking Duck Egg rolls, I could eat three orders just for dinner!
I ordered online for delivery and they refused to deliver the order or refund my money because they didnt have a delivery driver available.
A wonderful place for a special meal.

Not as good as it used to be. Barbarian Steak is probably pre-cooked. Server recommend it be made medium-rare but it came out over cooked and somehow cold? Ordered Pineapple and mango chicken but got Chicken and Peanuts instead (flavorless) and the Brandy Beef Noodles was bland, but was probably the best dish. Highlight of the night were the potstickers and the Dim Sum. It's a shame, because it used to be really good. Over-priced as well. Go elsewhere...
Great place to come with family
Good to take family here, love their fried rice, service was really nice, cozy spot

Love it . I read the reviews and take offense to the negative comments about the outside and decore . The store front in unique and charming , the interior is classy immaculately clean and comfortable . It was so calm and relaxing . The food was affordable and l o v e l y . Owner was attentive and personable . We thought we were just getting a snack, but the portions were a meal with a doggie bag . Tuesdays everything on the menu is 1195!
Wonderful food. Very casual interesting atmosphere the special on Tuesday is a great deal.

2019 first time back in five -7 years. Street parking , first floor so it looks accessible (threshold at front door floor and transition down 1/2-3/4 in to floor in back leading to bathroom area for those pushing wheelchairs). we have visited three times in last several months. we have had egg rolls each time good flavor , decorative on plate ( 2 egg rolls cut in half). wife had barbarian steak once and Hong Kong steak twice. Barbarian steak had good flavor , was a nice cut of meat, we prefer more veggies which you get with the Hong Kong steak, which had good taste and good quality meat. it came with all the veggies and mushrooms wife likes. I liked the honey walnut shrimp, good sized and not excessive batter to make shrimp look bigger. tried the barbarian steak which was good and a good cut of meat. tried a chicken dish that was below average but even in the best places the kitchen will have an off night. Food is consistently above average. I with  disagree with negative comments about quality of food. Comments about service being slow are correct. One waitress and owner working floor (maybe 16 customers) tonight.

This place is just absolutely horrible! My family and I used to come here many years ago when it was the original owner and restaurant and the food was pretty good. But now, oh man this place is bad. The food was subpar, overpriced for the quality, and the service was atrocious. Our waitress was clueless and unattenitive. There was a man that kept running back and forth when a private party arrived whom I assume was the owner and he displayed the same attitude. We weren't greeted when we arrived just asked how many. The place was practically empty when we showed up. There was only one couple seated in the restaurant when we arrived. We constantly had to keep asking the waitress for water, she would never come back to ask how everything was or if we needed anything more We had to clear our own plates and put them on a table next to us because the waitresses and owner were too busy tending to the private party and could care less about the 2 other tables that were dining there as well. A few of the appetizers were good but the mains were horrible. When we ordered our steak we were not asked how we wanted it cooked which I though was odd. We regretted  not saying anything because the Honk Kong steak was rare but the Barbarian steak or whatever it was called was charred and a little burnt. After being in the restaurant for a while, almost finished with our meal, the owner finally decided to greet us and ask us how everything was. I found this insulting considering the restaurant was pratically EMPTY and now he decided was the  time to acknowledge us. I can keep going on and on about how bad this place is but it will take me forever. We finally asked our waitress for our check when she decided to finally come out from wherever it was that she was hiding and it took her 20 minutes to bring it to us and then dissapeared again. I had to actually get up from my seat and say HELLO loudly for her to come out of hiding and take our credit card to charge us. Save yourself the time and aggravation and avoid this place at all costs. Chinatown has a lot better Chinese food than this. I would also reccomend New Star over this place anytime. We will never return to this place again.
I went there for the first time with a friend I loved it!
Great deal on Tuesday. Stumbled in and had a lovely meal.
Great food, Great service by Courtney, great presentation.
Highly recommend! Excellent food and service.  The owner greeted our table and was really nice and grateful.  We loved the pot stickers and beef chow fun!

Saw the dishes and was excited. Everything was either salty or flat tasting, except for the oxtail soup. Had xo chow fun, chive flower, garlic shrimp fried rice and nothing had that cooked in a wok smokiness or depth that I crave when eating Chinese... very meh.

A genuinely good Chinese restaurant, that gets little  press but deserves it. I am constantly looking for its mention in top 20 lists, where it clearly belongs. Dishes are made with flair and style. Has added an interesting concept Bento box, a mix of 4 or 5 small portions for a very reasonable price.  Very attractive  space.  Took 3 others, who are very picky, and they had a great time. Go

We had the pot stickers and pecking duck egg rolls, both delicious! For entrees, we had the spicy shrimp street noodles and the pork belly and chive flowers, which was absolutely amazing! And the service from Alan and his staff was excellent! Highly recommend this place & we will definitely be back!
Great food and a sufficient selection of appetizers and main Course entrees, along with the great service. You won't be disappointed. I know I wasn't.

After talking to some of the wait staff I’ve come to the understanding that the tips are not given to the waiter or waitress, but to the restaurant. This is incredibly deceitful. I’ll never come here again. Don’t get me wrong, the food is good. But I definitely don’t feel comfortable with a place that doesn’t want full disclosure.

Among the best Chinese food that I have eaten ANYWHERE.  Each dish is of very high quality.  Not a great location, but parking is often pretty easy.  The wait staff is not great, but they are responsive.

This is a great Chinese restaurant in a singularly weird place. Avondale on Milwaukee has changed, sure, but a first-rate Chinese restaurant on Milwaukee near Diversey? That's exactly what this is, though, so if you've got a need for Chinese food in an incredible setting (some of the best decor I've seen in any restaurant, Chinese or otherwise) this is it. And the ginger martini I had was great as well.

BEWARE GLUTEN ALLERGY!!! This food will make you very very sick. It’s unfortunate because it is high quality food but they tend to apply out of date presentation techniques (look at their restaurant design) and have not yet adapted to consumer demands. I doubt this once staple quality Chinese spot will make it Logan as we become more savvy to food safety. This place is highly gluten contaminated. Don’t even risk it if you’re gluten sensitive and lose a day of your life in pain as a result. The prices are only fair in theory if you’re not allergic to gluten and dine-in...I was initially impressed that it arrived in a cake box to impress me until I realized what a ridiculous environmental waste that is. I will never order from here again. Please be advised for your expectations that this is not a traditional Chinese takeout and you would be better off dining in than doing take out.
Aww
It was a bit over priced compared to the old Friendship that had more authentic chinese cuisine. 2 entrees, 2 apps, one drink, 2 sodas at $84..yikes!! Food was ok.  Pretty empty around 2pm.
Wow delicious.
We ordered delivery. The food was packaged with great care. The presentation was great even though it was takeout. The food was phenomenal.  Very fresh. Will definitely order again.

How the restaurant ruined my Christmas.  I've been going here for many years and have watched what use to be a good restaurant crumble. I literally ordered from Friendship at 4:30pm, hoping to treat myself to some overpriced Beef Chow Fun and some nice appetizers as I was solo this Christmas.  At 5:30pm the food was not delivered.  At 6pm I called the restaurant inquiring on my order, May asked for my name and said it was on its way, no more than 20 minutes away.  Given that the restaurant is literally 10 minutes from my house it was believable.  30 minutes later I called back saying it still hadn't arrived, she asked for my name again, it was still May who answered the phone, and she said, not to worry it was on its way.  10 minutes later, I decided to place a complaint with the online site i had ordered from, as it was now an hour past when it was supposed to be delivered, while chatting with the customer service agent, she said that the order had never been processed and would need to be canceled and reordered.  Meaning, that May over two phone calls had lied.  I was shocked. Having waited since 4:30pm for my food, expecting it at 5:30pm and it was now 7pm.  I then called the restaurant directly, and May was not apologetic, she was defensive saying she never lied and that she would have no idea what food or order was being delivered and what wasn't.  I explained to her, had i known that the issue an hour ago, I could have reordered and not still been waiting.  I was visibly upset, and she could not care less. I asked to speak with the owner, and he refused to get on the phone. As someone who likes to support neighborhood business and restaurants, i am shocked by this complete lack of care especially on Christmas.  I will not be ordering from Friendship again, and am going to look for a business that actually cares about my patronage and cares about customer service as the treatment I got from May on the phone was downright rude.  If you want overpriced, late delivery chinese food that doesn't care about your business...then this is your joint.,  Otherwise, I would recommend finding neighborhood places that care about their neighbors.
Food was superb! Server was exceptionally awesome. Can't wait to go back.
Great food and ambience!
Really good food, great atmosphere & can be a bit pricey
Amazing food and great decor! The place is really innovative chinese food but still has authentic flavors. One of my go to chinese places.
Came here for a private imperial dim sum tasting - incredible experience
Tuesdays they have a deal and tge food is fabulous
Excellent food and service. Never crowded. Been there several times for family celebrations
Really fresh and good . Some of the best chinese in the city

I want to give them a -5 because I just got off the phone with Alfredo "the manager" after 20mins of placing my order for them to tell me they had my card # wrong..  Mind you I gave it to the girl taking my order 3x. Supposedly the computer was down.  So after Alfredo is calling me asking for my card yet again. I'm like are you kidding me? So yes upset tone  This manager of Friendship has the nerve to say "well you still want it or not cause I'll just cancel?" Pregnant and craving Chinese.  Now very much 🤬
We stopped there for a late dinner.  They were not crowded at the time. The service was excellent and the food was great.
Phenomenal food and service
The food it is so soooooo good !!!!
Food had improved over the years! The Dim Sum is amazing
Nice spot for good Chinese if you're in the neighborhood
This was a restaurant that I went to for many years when was  across the street from the location now. I have been to this location too. I've never been disappointed there.
The atmosphere is amazing, good not so great.
Expensive and not worth it.
Food is always great
Great food and service.
Solid, elevated Chinese food.
Love, love, love this place. I've never had a dish that was bad. Well worth the price.
No, for these prices food should be made fresh not frozen,  orange chicken should be tender and juicy, not hard and chewy.
They never contacted me to tell me that I was outside of their delivery zone so I waited an hour and a half for food that never arrived.

Friendship has been a go to for years... Quality is always good, and their dishes are usually an interesting twist on a dish you're familiar with rather than the same old thing. I do wonder how many people order delivery or takeout from here because it's a huge space and is rarely crowded, but has remained open for years. It's a nice looking space worthy of taking a date. Definitely recommended!
Everything about this place is great
Food was disgusting and over priced well not go there again
Fancy Chinese food. It's good, not great, and on the pricey side. The decor and look of the place looks very nice.
Awesome food, awesome drinks

We've eaten at Friendship off and on over about 5 years. They've sometimes been closed at random times, which is frustrating. They seem to be open all recent times we've visited recently, though. They report a new menu, although I'm not sure quite how it's changed. Regardless the food has been quite good, and the service responsive. It's a nice step up from most Chinese restaurants, although the prices are still reasonable affordable. We enjoy Friendship and will be back again soon.
Pricey but high quality!

Usually Chinese restaurants in America fall into one of three categories: Chinatown, suburban buffet, and disgusting chop suey. Friendship brings forth a fourth category: authentic. Not heavy on salt and with no MSG, the dishes also lack sugary gravies. Service has been outstanding each time I have gone. But the wow factor indeed comes from flavorful dishes.

Not great for vegetarians. You will find exactly and only two things, spring rolls and a lo mein dish. The prices are steep here. The spring rolls weren't as extravagant as the price suggested, but I heard the lo mein is actually really good.
"Barbarian" steak lunch special is really good and only $10.
One of the best Chinese restaurant in Chicago. Not your typical Chinese restaurant.  Got to  try their Peking duck roll and Barbarian steak.

The last time I ordered, it seemed that they might have changed chefs, some of the old dishes were re-vamped, for the worse (i.e. Seafood nest).  I decided to give this place one last try.  Order was very late, called the restaurant and for 10 minutes no one answered the call. Finally got an answer and was told that the delivery driver will show up any second. 15 minutes go by and still no food. Manager calls me and offers me a 50% coupon for "dining-in only". What a cheapskate offer for a menu that's overpriced.  Save your money, go elsewhere.
Best egg rolls ever!
Excellent food great staff owner is an artist in presentation of food
Exquisite food.  High quality.  The spices are balanced perfectly to create the tastiest chinese food I have ever eaten.

We should have read the reviews... My wife said don't bother. Don't let other people shape your opinion. We were the only ones in here. One server. Plate presentation was great. However, one dish was undercooked. It was promptly corrected after I called the waiter over. $45 for two entrees, two teas and an app. Our experience paralleled many others...
Best food and best service I've ever experienced Logan Square. This is my new little oasis.
The chicken fried rice was delicious
Not your typical Chinese, but in a good way.   The food is inventive and great tasting.  I enjoy their appetizer sampler and calamari.
Too pricey for what it is, but food is mostly solid
I used to love this place. They changed their menu and everything tasted bland compared to when I first remembered it.
Very good quality food. Definitely worth a try

Much of the reviews are aligned with my own experience. The atmosphere was beautiful but cut by the radio station playing in the background... The food was very bland. 5 spice colimari was more like salt and pepper and that's about it some slight sauce smeared on the plate riddled with a handful of burnt dry red chilies. No sauce on the actual colimari. The fire in the bird's nest is a $17+ dish and they use FAKE crab... And what I can only describe as frozen scallops... Seriously?!. It's not the place I knew 5-6 years ago. I took a picture at 7pm... Completely dead empty. And over the coarse of an hour and a half 3 pick up orders. Service was horrible. Waitress/hostess was more interested in sitting in the back of the restaurant than helping us with our experience. I asked for to go boxes, signifying we were finished eating. She didn't offer deserts. She brought boxes and sat down. I had to get up and flag her down to get my check.
Great egg rolls great food been here many times never had a bad experience.
Definitely my favorite Chinese food in the area. Last time we were there the service was.... awkward. Hope it was just an off night.

Used to like this place. They changed their menu choices, changed how they make some of the dishes I've had before. Not for the better. They turned their crab rangoons into almost 100% cream cheese and onion. Little to no crab meat, disgusting.  Then we hoped that the main course would be a saving grace. Wow were we surprised. Have you ever eaten muscle-y, hard to chew chicken? If you havent, this place has it, both of our dishes had this nasty low grade chicken. Also had cartilege in it. The dishes go for 12-15 dollars. The manager was nice when I asked him to take my dish off my tab as I only took one bite out of it. The aesthetics and atmosphere is nice. This place used to be moderately priced, small portions and pretty good food. Now it's small portions and still high prices, hence the 1 star. Do not know what happened but we won't ever come back there. Ruined Valentine's Dinner.

We love this as a special date spot. We came here last Valentine's Day and enjoyed a really lovely evening. The wine list is great, their servers are amazingly friendly, and the food quality and presentation is great. Can't wait to come back again. They have excellent vegan dishes as well.
Delicious food and great service

OMG! The food was amazing! The chef came out to talk to all the guests. Made a special spectacular dish of his choice with a French touch! Invite the chef to create his miracle...  And the desert 😋😋😋 ........................., We are definitely coming back with our friends
Cool interior. But pricey for what you get.

Heard good things about this place and couldn't wait to try it. my grandmother and i ordered the friendship egg rolls and the vegetable egg rolls, both were excellent! She ordered the whitefish for dinner and I ordered the Honey Chicken. I loved the freshness of all of the dishes. The fish was lightly fried but didn't taste heavy. The Honey Chicken was EXCELLENT. The chicken was perfectly tender and the mix of vegetables was great. I can not wait to go back and get it again along with trying other things on the menu.  The only reason that it is not a full 5 stars is because the service was good but slow. The fish entree came out first and then we waited for the chicken for a good 5 minutes.  I will also say that if we were paying the full price (Tuesday is $10.95 entrees) I would have felt that the portions were a little light. I would have liked to have more veggies with the Honey Chicken (chicken portion seemed reasonable) and more fish (vegetable portion seemed reasonable).  All in all the food was excellent and I will happily give the service a second try.
Awesome! Great Server -Daniel is so Polite kind and Food is Better than it was  20 + years ago - Get the Duck roll!! - 😄
I order from here frequently - different, tasty and exciting Chinese food.  Delivery is always fast and eating-in is always interesting...the decor is really swank.
Bland, overpriced. I went here years ago and it was great, but this was like another restaurant entirely.

Horrible waiting time for delivery. Very good food but its so expensive. I know the owner wants to keep the quality but unless he brings down the pricing and gives more food per entree business is going to drop.
Great shrimp and fish!
Really good food. I would suggest it to anyone  .order in or go to the restaurant to eat too.

The service was a little strange here. There was plenty of staff around, but unclear who was attending to what. Menu items are meant to be shared, so going with two or more is a good option. Their pork belly was with chive flower was a pretty solid option.

I had the steak at 9pm it must of sat out all day.  It tasted like a gummy bear... Hello??!!!  Steak it not supposed to flop and be rubberized.  My stomach has been turning all night.  The meal from HELL.

Amazing food!!!!!! I loved the sweet and sour chicken and the wonton soup was extremely delicious! Our server was super nice...loved this place ..when I come back to Chicago I will definitely come back here!

Their Chinese Pancakes were so good! I didn't see them on the menu but found out they made them from a friend.  I thought the soy sauce was syrup several times and ruined my pancakes. Don't make the same mistakes, order shrimp fried rice and pancakes.
I am experiencing the same thing as NIzel. I will be declining the charge.

Ordered delivery over 2 hours ago and still no food. Tried calling 10 times and no answer then I tried my other phone and the guy picks up then promptly mumbles something before hanging up. Tried calling a couple more times before leaving a voicemail (it takes about 3 minutes before their voicemail kicks in) stating that I will be declining this charge unless someone gives me status on things. Still no response 30 minutes later so going to have to cancel the charge.  Edit: Now 30 minutes after I post the review they call me and say if I want the order, it will be there in 45 minutes. An hour later the order comes. They offered no apologies, no comp, no discount for a 3+ hour late order.  The food is AVERAGE and it cost $52 in total for barely any food. Literally at any other Chinese place what I ordered would've been a "Lunch or Dinner Special" for $5.95-$8.95 yet I paid $52 for this supposedly high-end garbage? No drinks thrown in, no specials, no coupons. For a Dragon Bao I expected a kick, but it was just a plain bao. Orange Chicken is sponge like and even though they threw oranges in the mix you don't taste them at all! 3 bite sized Egg rolls for $6.95? Ironically they threw in more dipping sauce than egg rolls and there's  hardly any Peking duck in them?  The teriyaki chicken fried rice was plain chicken fried rice. There was no hint of teriyaki in it at all. So they messed up my order as well.  To top it all off my fortune cookie read "Good things come to those that wait." What kind of madness is this? This goes on my do not recommend list.

Outstanding food and atmosphere. I have been going to FR since it re-opened back in the 90s. Over these nearly 20 year it has become my favorite restaurant in the city, even though it is a long haul from where i live. Initially I read a review in the Reader which intrigued me. Allen, the owner and chef, had come back to relaunch the family place. He transformed the cuisine by providing a cosmopolitan, and truly delicious re-imagining of Canton cuisine. I am a foody, but this place beats them all with its consistency and intimate atmosphere. Try the remarkable Long beans, the eggplant and bok choy, the peppercorn beef, and the whole snapper. I have held parties there for birthdays, as well as after conference dinners. Always a pleasure to go there. Try it, I guarantee you won't be disappointed.

The food was very good. Me and my boyfriend ordered teriyaki chicken fried rice (decided to give it a try; I usually order shrimp fried rice at traditional Chinese places), crab Rangoon and honey chicken (reminded me of orange chicken). Everything tastes great and the portions were big so we were able to split all the food and still had extra. The price is on the higher end (dishes start at like 13.95, and appetizers are 6.95 and up).

My friends, family and I celebrated my birthday here this September.  The decor is very different but beautiful.  Even though the bartender wasn't there that night the server made up for it.   He was very attentive but not overbearing. The appetizers were wonderful.   For our entries we had the Sesame Chicken, Barbarian Steak, Noodles Chow Mai and Chinese Green Beans.  Every single dish was hot, fresh, beautifully presented and delicious.  Though they don't serve coffee they accommodated us by serving hot, fresh coffee from the employees' pot.  I came from NW Indiana to try this place and will continue to patronize them when I am in Chicago.

So where do we began. First We purchased 1 honey chicken orange, 1 shrimp fried rice, 1 Veg chicken fun, 2 egg rolls, and had it delivered to the job. This meal was for 3 people and was shocked when we received the $59.00 bill. I was in shock  of how expensive the little meal was. I normally order Chinese and can feed a family of 4 for 40.00 and still have left overs. The last thing I was told they charged extra for Chinese broccoli. Ok but when I receive my order there was no Chinese broccoli. So I called the owner not only to tell him how bad the food was and believe me the shrimp rice was light in color with a grassy taste. The orange honey chicken had no flavor and the chicken taste old. If you are picky on where you dine and this is your first time here just beware. This review is just from my personal experience and not to slander or devalue this business. The truth is the truth and people need to know. Thanks

Walnut prawns are a must!  I'm also usually not a fortune cookie eater...but their's are delicious.  Never thought I'd say this.  Tuesday night dine in night for $9.95 any entree (plates are smaller) but still a good deal especially if with group sharing plates!

I use to love this place when I lived in Logan Square. Their food quality, flavors and service have gone downhill significantly since then. I ordered food on their website to the Lake location a few weekends ago and it ended in disaster. The estimated time of delivery was 1 hour but after 2 hours it still didn't come and I had to call them to have them send it. They had a lame excuse of "the Lake St Location is closed until spring". So the food came cold from the Logan Square location. They forgot my rice and crab rangoon. When I asked for a refund they told me I had to call a third party vendor managing their website. I shouldn't have to talk to a third party vendor to get my money back. My credit card company took care of the refund for me. The lady on the phone was rude. I will not be giving this place anymore of my business in the future.  [2014.05.18] Ordered again and same thing happened. I'm done with this place. 2 hours for food sitting and getting delivered is unacceptable business. I don't recommend ordering delivery from here.

Got the spicy peanut chicken, some steamed edamame (not on the menu,) and brown rice. As advertised, the chicken dish was a much improved version of Kung Pao chicken. Spicy and rich but not obnoxious.  My knocks on the place: no steamed edamame on the menu (though the wok-tossed sounded good, we are counting calories,) and brown rice doesn't come as an alternative - must order completely additionally. KPC, brown rice and edamame delivered came out to $30. Kind of expensive, even including a delivery charge.
We have only dined here once, it was fine, we ordered delivery from here several times. Nothing great, but it is good.
Amazing!  My family got 4 dishes and family styled it, each dish was better than the last.  Definitely coming back!

When a Chinese restaurant is full of nothing but older white people, you may want to go to another Chinese restaurant. (nothing against older white people, my parents are older white people).  Back to the restaurant. The decor is the best thing about this place - lots of Buddha heads. The only reason we went here is Groupon (thanks for nothing, G). Got the roll to start - meh, had better, but not horrible. Don't remember what hubby got, but I got a vegetarian eggplant dish. I LOVE eggplant, I grow it in my garden, I buy it, I roast it, I bake it, I mix it with other veggies etc. This eggplant was so bad, I could not eat it. The worst eggplant that has ever came out of my kitchen would blow FCR's eggplant away. Not only was it so undercooked, I had to question whether they actually applied temperature to it or was the sauce the only thing warming it up. And speaking of the sauce - what sauce? Normally, a "Chinese Eggplant" dish is succulent, swimming in delicious brown sauce, soft and spicy. This was hard, dry and bland.  My husband forgot his credit card, so we had to come back and figured since a few reviews mention their crab rangoon as being good, we won't waste the drive up here and order some - FAIL, too rich, yet still tasteless. Never. Again. Oh, and they don't have a sweet-and-sour soup on the menu. What kind of Chinese place does not have s'n's soup?!

One of the more innovative Chinese restaurants in Logan Square, don't come here expecting greasy noodles and traditional dishes. They've recently updated their menu to include items like "Barbarian" steak (a play on Mongolian beef) and firecracker chicken lo mein (a personal favorite). The prices are noticeably higher than the average takeout place but the portions and quality are noticeably better. Also, the cool decor – wall of Buddha heads and kimono statue – make this a great neighborhood date spot.
Always a dining pleasure coming here. I've been coming here since it first opened. I'm never disappointed!
This place is by far the best chinese restaurant west of ashland!  I order to take out frequently and this is a great place to dine-in as well
An amazing restaurant with very good and diverse food selection.

A hidden gem in logan square! Food is delicious! A nice twist on regular chinese food. 1/2 price entrees on Tue. A must for a date night. Quite and romantic setting. Staff is friendly and nice. Prices are good.

Back when I first discovered some of the best Chinese in Chicago this restaurant was still not very well known. Since 2007 I have been numerous times and every time is just as good. It's gotten busier over the years but the sesame chicken and egg rolls are amazing! Definitely worth the trip and should be frequented often.

Friendship Chinese is one of my favorite Chinese restaurants in the city. My favorite dishes are the shrimp and pineapple fried rice, the beef and broccoli and the eggrolls. It's a fun, casual dinner spot.

If you like Chinese food, this is an ideal place for a quiet, affordable dinner with your better half. Recommended are General Tso's chicken and the potstickers; for the less adventurous you can't go wrong with beef & peapods and chicken fried rice. A little out of the way and parking may be hard, but if you're in the 'hood Friendship is worth a try even if you're ordering carry-out.

Friendship can be a bit expensive, they do have days where they offer up specials that make it so worth it. Their food is fresh and is prepared to your liking. Its a very odd place for such a good place to be located but its really good
Great food but the menu keeps changing and my favorite food keeps on getting removed.  I love coming to the restraunt if the food would stay the same.

Best Chinese food in Logan Square, possibly in the city! I HIGHLY recommend the Pineapple Shrimp Fried Rice. Have had take-out, delivery and eaten in the restaurant. Service is great no matter your method of dining.

The most decadent and delicious Chinese Food I've eaten. The Sesame Beef and Honey Walnut Shrimp were my favorite on the menu, and the proportions were great. The best bang for your buck are the $8.95 lunch specials and because it comes with rice and wonton soup! Also, Tuesdays they have a special as well. The service was pretty good except for one encounter with a rude waitress. Otherwise, I highly recommend this place.
there has been a few changes so some favorite dishes are no longer available, but worth a try again. Has specials on Tuesday nites and lunch specials as well.

For as long as I can remember this restaurant had the best Chinese food in Chicago... I was hooked on their BBQ pork and beef fried rice.... Omg... the best! Well tonight i decided to order from them for the first time in about 4 years and I was almost heartbroken at the drastic change from delicious to almost garbage. They don't even have BBQ pork on the menu!  I know this place has to have a new owner because it just doesn't make sense otherwise... and then the prices are too much... whoever owns this place now should change the name, the real Friendship restaurant died when they decided it was more about the look and cost than the quality in the food... I'm sorry but I know Whole in the wall spots better and cheaper!
Great food, awesome decor, and OK service.  I will definitely be back.

I've been looking forward to trying this restaurant out for a long time and was really disappointed from the second we walked in.  We got in an hour before closing time (my boyfriend and I have both worked in the service industry and try to avoid walking in at closing time) and were met with a dirty look from the hostess.  Barely acknowledged, we were led to our seats.  The service was terrible, we never had the same person come up to us, always different, so we didn't know who our server was.  Nobody came to get our order in the 20 minutes we were sitting there until we mentioned it to the hostess, receiving another dirty look.  Our appetizer (crab rangoon) was amazing and things started to look up... until it didn't.  We had been in the restaurant a full hour and didn't have our entrees.  The food was horrible.  The website and menu present an upgraded chinese experience but seemed more of a rip off.  Fancy titles and ingredients for dishes that would be better at Panda Express.  No offense to anyone, but the fact that there were no asians or chinese patrons should have been the first red flag.  Americans who are not used to authentic asian food may be fooled, but I will never go there again.  I've had better chinese from the corner, storefront chinese restaurants where you can get a full meals worth for less than $10.
Good food, nice amnience

We probably order from the Logan Square location once a week!  It's a terrible habit because it can get expensive, but after a long day nothing is better than an egg roll and their won ton soup; I highly recommend it! I just wish we could order sushi from this location as well! :)
